Example
These results are only an estimation of the amount of energy in the food
being tested. If you look at the nutritional label on the food’s packaging,
the real energy content is likely to be higher.
That’s because quite a bit of energy in the food is transferred to the
environment rather than being used to raise the temperature of the water.
Food scientists use fancy machines called calorimeters to measure the
energy content of our food — they’re insulated and sealed, so produce much
more accurate results than any experiment that could be done in school.
